text: Quitman is a city in the state of Texas in the United States. It is the county seat of Wood County. About 1,942 people lived there in 2020. It was named for John A. Quitman, a governor of Mississippi. Sissy Spacek was born in Quitman. == References == == Other websites == Category:County seats in Texas Category:Cities in Texas
title: Quitman, Texas
